-- CTC Media’s Moscow Audience Falls in Week to June 3, TNS Says
-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 2012-06-05T23:03:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-05/ctc-media-s-moscow-audience-falls-in-week-to-june-3-tns-says.html
CTC Media Inc. (CTCM) ’s average daily share
of viewers in Moscow aged 18-years-old and above fell to 5.3
percent in the week to June 3, data compiled by TNS-Global show.  The share of viewers in Moscow for the CTC TV channel, the
Nasdaq-listed Russian media company’s biggest source of revenue,
declined from 5.8 percent in the week to May 27. CTC slipped
behind REN TV, becoming the sixth-most watched television
channel in Moscow, data researcher TNS-Global said in an e-mail
today.  NTV Television, Pervyi Kanal, Rossiya-1 and TNT also ranked
ahead of CTC among Moscow viewers in the week to June 3, TNS-
Global data show.  The average daily audience among viewers four-years-old and
over in Moscow for CTC fell to 6 percent in the week to June 3
from 6.6 percent in the previous week. CTC remained the fifth-
most-watched in audience rankings in the week to June 3, the
data show. NTV Television, Pervyi Kanal, Rossiya-1 and TNT
ranked ahead of CTC, TNS-Global said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
